In a multi-dimensional array like `int[][][] a = new int[5][5][5]`,
one has to specify indices of all dimensions to access an element
(e.g., one can access `a[1][1][1]`, but `a[1][1]` is illegal).

frontmatter.shortDescription: Only the elements of the innermost array of a multi-dimensional array are accessible
frontmatter.shortCorrection: Also the elements of outer arrays of a multi-dimensional array are accessible
